---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout title="FAQ — ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" description="Frequently asked questions about ScrabbleWordsFinder.com. Learn about our free word solver, dictionaries, achievements, privacy, and more." keywords="scrabble word finder faq, scrabble solver help, free scrabble tool questions">

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-4 pb-6">
    <a href="/" class="text-sm text-blue-400 hover:underline mb-6 inline-block">← Back to Solver</a>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-8">Everything you need to know about ScrabbleWordsFinder.com</p>

    <div class="space-y-6">

      <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900/50 p-4 open:border-purple-800/50">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 group-open:text-blue-400">
          What is ScrabbleWordsFinder.com?
          <span class="text-gray-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">ScrabbleWordsFinder.com is a free, instant word solver for Scrabble and other word games. Enter your tiles and get every valid word ranked by score — no sign-up, no waiting. It works as you type with results updating in real time.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900/50 p-4 open:border-purple-800/50">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 group-open:text-blue-400">
          Is it really free?
          <span class="text-gray-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">Yes, completely free. No premium tiers, no per-day limits, no paywalls. You don't need to create an account, enter an email, or sign up for anything. Open the page and start solving immediately.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900/50 p-4 open:border-purple-800/50">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 group-open:text-blue-400">
          What dictionaries are supported?
          <span class="text-gray-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">We support SOWPODS (used internationally, 335,000+ words) and TWL (Tournament Word List, used in North America). You can switch between them using the dictionary selector on the solver page. Both include words from 2 to 15 letters.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900/50 p-4 open:border-purple-800/50">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 group-open:text-blue-400">
          How do blank tiles work?
          <span class="text-gray-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">Enter a question mark (?) for each blank tile. The solver will try every possible letter in that position and show you all valid words. You can use up to 2 blanks in a standard Scrabble game. Words made with blanks score 0 for the blank letter.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900/50 p-4 open:border-purple-800/50">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 group-open:text-blue-400">
          How do I save words?
          <span class="text-gray-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">Click any word in the results to save it to your 👑 Memory Workbench collection. The word is stored in your browser's localStorage and a dictionary definition is fetched automatically. You can download your memory workbench or back them up via your UUID in <a href="/settings" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Settings</a>.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900/50 p-4 open:border-purple-800/50">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 group-open:text-blue-400">
          How do achievements work?
          <span class="text-gray-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
          <p class="mb-2">When you click a word in the results, the Tile Scores panel shows your score and awards an achievement level:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>⭐ Rising Star (1–9 pts)</li>
            <li>👍 Word Builder (10–19 pts)</li>
            <li>🔥 Hot Streak (20–29 pts)</li>
            <li>🏆 Triple Threat (30–49 pts)</li>
            <li>🌟 Scrabble Legend (50+ pts)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-2">Click "Save" to file the achievement with an optional note. View all your achievements on the <a href="/achievements" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Achievements page</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900/50 p-4 open:border-purple-800/50">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 group-open:text-blue-400">
          What does the 💎 diamond icon mean?
          <span class="text-gray-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">Words with a 💎 icon score more than 20 points. These are high-value plays worth considering for your next move.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900/50 p-4 open:border-purple-800/50">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 group-open:text-blue-400">
          Is my data private?
          <span class="text-gray-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">Yes. The word solver works entirely client-side — your tiles never leave your browser. Memory Workbench are stored locally. We collect anonymous click data (country, device type) to improve features but never collect personal information. No email or account is required. Read our full <a href="/privacy" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900/50 p-4 open:border-purple-800/50">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 group-open:text-blue-400">
          How many letters can I enter?
          <span class="text-gray-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">The Word Solver accepts up to 15 letters (the maximum word length in Scrabble). The Tile Rack accepts 7 tiles (your standard rack). Both sync bidirectionally — type in either one.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900/50 p-4 open:border-purple-800/50">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 group-open:text-blue-400">
          How do I report a bug?
          <span class="text-gray-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">Click the 🐛 Bug icon in the toolbar or go to our <a href="/contact?subject=bug" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Contact page</a> and select "Bug Report" as the subject. Tell us what happened, what browser you're using, and what you expected. We investigate all reports.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-800 bg-gray-900/50 p-4 open:border-purple-800/50">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-gray-200 group-open:text-blue-400">
          Can I use this for Words With Friends?
          <span class="text-gray-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-400">Yes! While the dictionaries are optimised for Scrabble (SOWPODS/TWL), most words are valid in Words With Friends too. The scoring will differ since WWF uses different tile values, but the word validity is largely the same.</p>
      </details>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 text-center">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Still have questions?</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-3 rounded-xl bg-blue-500 text-gray-950 font-semibold hover:bg-blue-400 transition-colors">
        ✉️ Contact Us
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is ScrabbleWordsFinder.com?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com is a free, instant word solver for Scrabble and other word games. Enter your tiles and get every valid word ranked by score — no sign-up, no waiting." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is ScrabbleWordsFinder really free?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, completely free. No premium tiers, no per-day limits, no paywalls. No account creation needed." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What dictionaries does ScrabbleWordsFinder support?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "SOWPODS (335,000+ words, international) and TWL (Tournament Word List, North America). Both include words from 2 to 15 letters." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do blank tiles work in the solver?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Enter a question mark (?) for each blank tile. The solver tries every letter in that position and shows all valid words you can make." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do I save words?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Click any word in the results to save it to your Memory Workbench collection with an auto-fetched definition. Words persist in your browser." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do achievements work?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Click a word to see your score in the Tile Scores panel. Scores are awarded achievement levels from Rising Star (1-9 pts) to Scrabble Legend (50+ pts). Click Save to file them permanently." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is my data private on ScrabbleWordsFinder?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. The solver works client-side — tiles never leave your browser. We collect only anonymous analytics. No email or account required." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many letters can I enter?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Up to 15 letters in the Word Solver, or 7 tiles in the Tile Rack. Both sync bidirectionally." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do I report a bug?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Click the bug icon in the toolbar or visit the Contact page with Bug Report selected. Include browser details and what you expected." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can I use ScrabbleWordsFinder for Words With Friends?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! Most words valid in Scrabble are also valid in Words With Friends, though tile scoring differs between the two games." } }
  ]
}
</script>
</Layout>
